title: Basic Usage
text: download specific data, instance monthly Fama/French 5 Factors (2x3) set can use: return object class french_dataset: file contains two subsets data: first one default one unnamed, second one “Annual Factors: January-December”. can access data first subset: can now browse use data.frame directly, instance, plot factors risk-free rate overtime: can browse details page specific data set using:
code: ff_5_factors <-   download_french_data("Fama/French 5 Factors (2x3)") #> New names: #> * `` -> ...1 #> New names: #> * `` -> ...1 ff_5_factors #>  #> ── Kenneth's French data set #> ℹ This file was created by CMPT_ME_BEME_OP_INV_RETS using the 202106 CRSP database. The 1-month TBill return is from Ibbotson and Associates Inc.  #>  #> Information collected from: https://mba.tuck.dartmouth.edu/pages/faculty/ken.french/ftp/F-F_Research_Data_5_Factors_2x3_CSV.zip on Wed Sep 08 20:57:17 2021 #>  #> ℹ For details on the data set call the function `browse_details_page()` on this object #>  #> ── Subsets in the file: #> # A tibble: 2 × 2 #>   name                               data                    #>   <chr>                              <list>                  #> 1 ""                                 <spec_tbl_df [696 × 7]> #> 2 "Annual Factors: January-December" <spec_tbl_df [57 × 7]> ff_5_factors$subsets #> # A tibble: 2 × 2 #>   name                               data                    #>   <chr>                              <list>                  #> 1 ""                                 <spec_tbl_df [696 × 7]> #> 2 "Annual Factors: January-December" <spec_tbl_df [57 × 7]> monthly_ff_5_factors <- ff_5_factors$subsets$data[[1]] monthly_ff_5_factors #> # title: Basic Usage
text: can also save original uncompressed file downloading reading , specifying valid path name: download file, read , assign result object ff_5_factors, save results file fama_french_5_factors.zip current directory. prefer use original file name just leave dest_file parameter unset:
code: ff_5_factors <-   download_french_data("Fama/French 5 Factors (2x3)",                        dir = ".",                        dest_file = "fama_french_5_factors.zip") ff_5_factors <-   download_french_data("Fama/French 5 Factors (2x3)",                        dir = ".")

title: Download the data set — download_french_data
text: dataset_name string data set name. Use get_french_data_list() get list data sets available download. dir character. valid directory path save compressed downloaded file. dest_file character. valid file name save compressed downloaded file. dir defined dest_file left empty, original file name used. overwrite boolean. Overwrite existing file? max_tries numeric. Number file download trials.

title: Download the data set — download_french_data
text: objects class french_dataset following elements: info - holds information information retrieved. details_url - url webpage details data set. subsets tibble subsets contained downloaded file, tibble contains name data column.
